The paper discusses the convergence and complexity of Deep Neural Networks, with a particular focus on Convolutional Neural Networks. This topic falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Information Theory (cs.IT). Given the emphasis on deep learning and neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI. The mention of complexity and theoretical guarantees also suggests cs.IT as a possible sub-category.
